00:51:28,794 --> 00:51:30,545
I'm happy to help.

781
00:51:36,552 --> 00:51:38,553
You brighten my spirits.

782
00:51:42,099 --> 00:51:45,059
Well, I think I may
be able to brighten them a bit more.

783
00:51:47,396 --> 00:51:48,980
You don't know it yet,

784
00:51:50,816 --> 00:51:53,276
but Saturday is going to be a red-letter day

785
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:57,030
in the life of Dr. Bertram Chickering Jr.

786
00:51:58,199 --> 00:51:59,657
- Oh?
- Mmm.

787
00:52:03,704 --> 00:52:04,704
Um...

788
00:52:06,081 --> 00:52:07,874
Is it some kind of a holiday?

789
00:52:09,251 --> 00:52:11,461
Yeah, you could call it that.

790
00:52:12,046 --> 00:52:13,213
Uh...

791
00:52:13,589 --> 00:52:16,466
Cecily is visiting her brother at Harvard

792
00:52:16,550 --> 00:52:18,718
and won't be back until Sunday,

793
00:52:18,803 --> 00:52:23,348
so that means we have my apartment
all to ourselves.

794
00:52:34,819 --> 00:52:36,027
Is that for the ball?

795
00:52:38,781 --> 00:52:40,573
Yes.

796
00:52:42,785 --> 00:52:44,452
Once this procedure is done,

797
00:52:44,537 --> 00:52:47,163
no one will stare at them like freaks,

798
00:52:47,248 --> 00:52:49,332
like they're monsters.

799
00:52:49,416 --> 00:52:52,752
Can you imagine how they'll feel
when they're finally normal?

800
00:52:54,338 --> 00:52:55,964
No...

801
00:52:56,048 --> 00:52:58,132
I can't.

802
00:52:58,259 --> 00:53:00,760
Oh, that's not what I meant.

803
00:53:00,845 --> 00:53:03,388
- I'm sorry. I just get excited.
- Stop it, John.

804
00:53:04,431 --> 00:53:06,599
I am what I am and I can live with that.

805
00:53:07,935 --> 00:53:09,561
But I can't live like this.

806
00:53:10,521 --> 00:53:11,604
I don't understand.

807
00:53:11,689 --> 00:53:13,523
I can't live with you here, John.

808
00:53:17,152 --> 00:53:19,404
You arrived one night and you were back.

809
00:53:21,782 --> 00:53:24,325
You needed me and I wanted that.

810
00:53:26,620 --> 00:53:29,706
So I wait for your knock on my door.

811
00:53:29,790 --> 00:53:32,792
No matter what the hour, I wait here,

812
00:53:34,587 --> 00:53:36,212
hoping you'll come.

813
00:53:37,715 --> 00:53:40,884
Even though I know
you've just been with some other woman.

814
00:53:40,968 --> 00:53:42,218
Abby.

815
00:53:42,303 --> 00:53:45,138
And you have every right.
I have no claim on you.

816
00:53:47,308 --> 00:53:50,393
What could a woman like me
rightly expect from any man?

817
00:53:53,981 --> 00:53:55,481
But it's too hard now...

818
00:53:57,651 --> 00:53:59,569
Knowing we'll never be together.

819
00:54:02,448 --> 00:54:06,409
I can't fool myself any longer and it's...

820
00:54:06,493 --> 00:54:08,494
Being near you is just too painful.

821
00:54:10,205 --> 00:54:12,332
- Abby, I love you.
- Oh.

822
00:54:12,416 --> 00:54:14,083
I never stopped.

823
00:54:14,168 --> 00:54:15,627
You only come here to talk.

824
00:54:15,711 --> 00:54:18,713
You go elsewhere for everything else.

825
00:54:19,131 --> 00:54:20,548
Please just leave.

826
00:54:21,342 --> 00:54:23,009
Abby.

827
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:24,761
I need you to go.

828
00:54:28,849 --> 00:54:30,850
No.

